As someone of Vietnamese descent, I can confidently say that Nha Trang Vietnamese Canteen is one of the most authentic Vietnamese restaurants one can find in HK. Even the chefs and staff are mostly Viet, which is quite rare.

When one walks into the restaurant, you will be greeted by a colourful, quirky interior that takes inspiration from a street food scene out of Ho Chi Minh City. I was very pleasantly surprised by its cleanliness - Having eaten at many medium-scale restaurants in HK during busy lunch hours, I’ve learnt to cope with overseeing small cleanliness hiccups (tissues on the floor, sticky tables, ... you name it!), but there truly was nothing to criticise about at Nha Trang Canteen. Cuddos to the management team! 

The food is definitely authentic and pretty good for HK standard - Though if you expect Vietnam-level authenticity, you will be disappointed. 

We ordered three dishes:

(1) Spring rolls - I loved the presentation and generous portion of herbs and vegetable that accompanied the dish. Though the spring rolls were on the smaller side, the taste was authentic.

(2) Pork chop with rice - This was definitely the highlight of our lunch. Caramelised to perfection with just the right amount of charcoal taste. Highly recommended!

(3) Bun rieu - I was really excited to try out this dish as it’s one of my favourite Viet soup noodle dishes (even more than the glorious pho). Unfortunately, I was let down. It certainly didn’t taste bad, but did not live up to my expectations in terms of flavour.
So so

味道不錯
